    Stringable

    public class NEATRecombiner
extends Recombiner<NEATGenotype>
    Implements recombination as described by the NEAT evolutionary algorithm (See https://www.cs.ucf.edu/~kstanley/neat.html) but generalised to any number of parents: if one parent dominates all others then the new genotype will inherit the genes of this parent, otherwise the genes from all parents will be inherited (except in the case where adding a synapse would result in a cycle and recurrent networks are not allowed). The values of the alleles of inherited genes are based on the values of the alleles of all parents that possess that gene.
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman
